msgSnippet: Jason, surely you just send emails to junit@yahoogroups.com and the mail engine forwards on.  Your mail server doesn t know who s on the list. FYI, I don t get
messageBody:
Jason, surely you just send emails to junit@yahoogroups.com and the mail engine forwards on.  Your mail server doesn't know who's on the list.
 
FYI, I don't get the error messages.
-----Original Message-----
From: Jason Rogers [mailto:jason.rogers@...]
Sent: 14 June 2001 22:21
To: 'junit@yahoogroups.com'
Subject: [junit] failure messages

Is anyone else getting these failure messages every time they send a mail to
the group?  The messages start with:

[005] Mail retry count exceeded sending to:
  WESTPAC   /NGS011

If so, is there anyway to figure out whose account this is and disable it
for the time being?  I suspect what is happening is that someone's mailbox
is full and is not allowing more mail to come in.

-Jason
